  "statement": {
    "title": "torch.masked.mean on bool tensor silently accumulates in bool dtype, clamping totals",
    "body": "`torch.masked.mean` with a bool input tensor infers `dtype=torch.bool` for the internal sum, so any count of 2 or more reduces to `True` (1). The result is wrong instead of raising an error. Fix: explicitly reject non-floating/complex dtypes with a clear `ValueError`.",
    "labels": ["module: masked", "topic: numerical"]
  },
